The Limpopo High Court sentenced Jeffrey Seerane, Andrew Milanzi and James Serake on Tuesday to a combined 46 years behind bars for the murder of a Pakistani shop owner in Tubatse in 2015. Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe indicated that the Police welcomed the sentence and hoped it would send a clear message to would-be criminals that crimes does not pay. The three were found guilty of the killing of Mohammed Nawaz during a robbery at his shop on 7 August 2015. Ngoepe indicated that they had entered the shop in Ga-Mashamothane village at about 18:00 and opened fire, shooting Nawaz in the head. They also shot and injured Nawaz s father and a shopper before fleeing the scene with several airtime vouchers, cigarettes, groceries and an undisclosed amount of cash. The of the men were sentenced to life imprisonment for murder, 15 years for robbery with aggravating circumstances and six years for attempted murder. Acting Provincial Commissioner Jan Scheepers has commended the Tubatse Police on an excellent job. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com